<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="322" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-02-07"><hi rend="italic">February 7,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 109.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I herewith inclose originals in English
                            and in Spanish of the protocol between the American and the Dominican
                            Governments signed by me in virtue of the full powers telegraphed on
                            February 6 by the President of the United States to the President of the
                            Dominican Republic.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">T. C. Dawson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>